      <text bytes="690" xml:space="preserve">In [[telecommunication]], a '''recovery procedure''' is a process that attempts to bring a [[communications system|system]] back to a normal operating state. Examples:
#The actions necessary to restore an [[automated information system]]'s [[data file]]s and computational capability after a system failure. 
#In [[data communications]], a process whereby a data station attempts to resolve conflicting or erroneous conditions arising during the [[data transfer]].

